  "prompt": "How many Knights of the Round Table were there?",
  "response": "The number of Knights of the Round Table varies depending on the source and the particular legend. In Arthurian lore, the Round Table is said to have been created by Merlin to prevent quarrels among Arthur's knights over who should sit where, as everyone seated at a round table is considered equal.\n\nThe most commonly cited number is around 12 to 150 Knights of the Round Table. However, the exact number is not consistent across different stories. Some of the most famous knights include:\n\n1. **King Arthur**\n2. **Sir Lancelot**\n3. **Sir Gawain**\n4. **Sir Percival**\n5. **Sir Galahad**\n6. **Sir Bedivere**\n7. **Sir Kay**\n8. **Sir Tristan**\n9. **Sir Gareth**\n10. **Sir Bors**\n\nThese are just a few of the many knights who are often mentioned in various tales. The legends of King Arthur and his knights have been told and retold in many forms, leading to variations in the number and names of the knights.",
